# TypeScript: imports section divider

For **`*.ts`** and **`*.tsx`** files that contain any **`import`** statements (including **`import type`**):

1. Put **all** import lines together at the **top** of the file.
2. **Allowed above imports:** a shebang (`#!`), **`/// <reference … />`** directives, or other tooling-required headers that must be first.
3. Immediately **after** the last import line, add **two identical full-line slash dividers**, **then exactly one blank line**, then everything else (types, exports, implementation, `export … from` re-exports).

Use **this exact shape** (two identical full lines of **`/`** only, then one blank line before the next line of code). Match the length already used in this repo (both lines must be identical):

```ts
///////////////////////////
///////////////////////////

```

Do **not** place types, exports, or non-import code between imports and this divider.

## When to omit

If the file has **no** `import` statements, **do not** add this divider.

## Relation to other layout rules

The **Supporting functions** banner (see **`.cursor/rules/function-declaration-and-file-layout.mdc`**) stays **below** the implementation section as documented there — it does not replace the imports divider.
